-- Nigeria Sold 134.6 Billion Naira of Bills in Open-Market Auction
-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 2012-03-24T10:29:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/nigeria-sold-134-6-billion-naira-of-bills-in-open-market-auction.html
Nigeria  sold 134.6 billion naira
($862.8 million) of treasury bills in an auction at its open-
market operations.  The  Central Bank  of Nigeria yesterday auctioned 59.4
billion naira of 258-day bills at 15.25 percent and 75.2 billion
naira of 335-day debt at 15.37 percent, it said in an e-mailed
statement today. Bids totaled 296.8 billion naira, more than
double the amount on offer.  Open-market operations are used by the Abuja, Nigeria-based
bank to control short-term interest rate and money supply in the
economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emele Onu in Lagos at 
